## {{ rule.title }}

The total allowed Foreign Tax Credit on [Form 1116](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1116) is the baseline [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) credit plus any treaty re-sourcing additional credit, subject to the [Form 1116](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1116) line 33 nonrefundable-credit cap. This is the final FTC number that flows into Schedule 3 and ultimately reduces your regular tax for payment/refund computation.

{% set base = rule.inputs_by_key["us.stage.baseline_allowed_ftc"].value | from_json -%}
{% set add = rule.inputs_by_key["us.stage.treaty_additional_ftc"].value | from_json -%}
{% set allowed = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
For 2025:

- Baseline allowed FTC from US25-14 (lesser of available foreign tax and [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) limit, summed across baskets): **{{ base.total_allowed_ftc_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Treaty re-sourcing additional FTC from US25-18 ([Pub. 514](https://www.irs.gov/publications/p514) worksheet line 21, capped by [Form 1116](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1116) line 33): **{{ add.treaty_resourcing_additional_ftc_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- **Total allowed FTC after treaty re-sourcing:** **{{ allowed.total_allowed_ftc_after_treaty_resourcing_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**

This is the number that subtracts from regular tax at US25-21 ([Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) line 22) and is reported on Schedule 3 line 1.

